%F A002026 Number of (s(0), s(1), ..., s(n)) such that s(i) is a nonnegative integer, s(0) = 0 = s(n), s(1) = 1, |s(i) - s(i-1)| <= 1 for i >= 2, Also T(n, n), where T is the array defined in A026105.
%F A002026 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n-1} Sum_{i=0..k} C(k, 2i)*A000108(i+1). - _Paul Barry_, Jul 18 2003
%F A002026 G.f.: 4*z/(1-z+sqrt(1-2*z-3*z^2))^2. - _Emeric Deutsch_, Dec 27 2003
%F A002026 a(n) = A005043(n+2) - A005043(n). - _Paul Barry_, Apr 17 2005
%F A002026 D-finite with recurrence: (n+3)*a(n) +(-3*n-4)*a(n-1) +(-n-1)*a(n-2) +3*(n-2)*a(n-3)=0. - _R. J. Mathar_, Dec 03 2012
%F A002026 a(n) ~ 3^(n+3/2) / (sqrt(Pi)*n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 01 2014
%F A002026 G.f.: A(z) satisfies z*A(z) = (1-z)*M(z) - 1, where M(z) is the g.f. of A001006. - _Gennady Eremin_, Feb 09 2021
%F A002026 a(0) = 0, a(1) = 1; a(n) = 2 * a(n-1) + a(n-2) + Sum_{k=0..n-3} a(k) * a(n-k-3). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Nov 09 2021
%F A002026 G.f.: x*M(x)^2 where M(x) = (1 - x - sqrt(1 - 2*x - 3*x^2)) / (2*x^2) is the g.f. of the Motzkin numbers A001006. - _Peter Bala_, Feb 05 2024
